MetaDimension.name: Period
MetaDimension.basedOn:
DECLARE @strSQLCommand nvarchar(2000) DECLARE @strTableName nvarchar(100)
SET @strTableName = '{DataSource.Company}$Accounting Period'
IF EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM INFORMATION_SCHEMA.COLUMNS WHERE TABLE_NAME = @strTableName + ' GB' AND COLUMN_NAME='Period End') BEGIN SET @strTableName = @strTableName + ' GB' SET @strSQLCommand = 'SELECT [Year]*100+ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY [Year] ORDER BY m.[Period Start]) as [Period.PeriodId], m.[Period Name]+'' ''+y.[Period Name] as [Period.Name], [Year] as [Period.Year], ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY [Year] ORDER BY m.[Period Start]) as [Period.PeriodInYear], m.[Period Start] as [Period.PeriodStart], m.[Period End] as [Period.PeriodEnd], m.[Period Start] as [Period.PeriodStart2], m.[Period End] as [Period.PeriodEnd2], case when ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY [Year] ORDER BY m.[Period Start])=1 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END as [Period.NewFiscalYear], [Closed] as [Period.Closed] FROM (SELECT [Period Start], CASE WHEN [Period End]<[Period Start] THEN ''2099-12-31'' ELSE [Period End] END as [Period End], [Period Name] as PeriodInYear,[Period Name],[Closed] FROM [' + @strTableName + '] WHERE [Period Type]=2) m JOIN (SELECT [Period Start], [Period End],datepart(yyyy,dateadd(MM,1,[Period Start])) as [Year],[Period Name] as [Period Name] FROM [' + @strTableName + '] WHERE [Period Type]=4) y ON m.[Period Start] BETWEEN y.[Period Start] AND CASE WHEN y.[Period End]<y.[Period Start] THEN ''2099-12-31'' ELSE y.[Period End] END' END ELSE BEGIN DECLARE @firstYear int DECLARE @strPeriodStart nvarchar(100) DECLARE @strPeriodEnd nvarchar(100) DECLARE @strFiscal nvarchar(100) DECLARE @strYear nvarchar(250)
SET @strFiscal = '[New Fiscal Year]' SET @strPeriodStart = '[Starting Date]' IF EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM INFORMATION_SCHEMA.COLUMNS WHERE TABLE_NAME = @strTableName AND COLUMN_NAME='Ending Date') SET @strPeriodEnd = '[Ending Date]' ELSE SET @strPeriodEnd = 'DATEADD(DAY,-1,DATEADD(MONTH,1,[Starting Date]))' SET @firstYear = ( SELECT TOP 1 DATEPART(YEAR,[Starting Date]) as [Year] FROM [{DataSource.Company}$Accounting Period] WHERE [Starting Date]<(SELECT MAX([Starting Date]) FROM ( SELECT TOP 2 [Starting Date] FROM [{DataSource.Company}$Accounting Period] WHERE [New Fiscal Year]=1 ORDER BY [Starting Date] ) p ) ORDER BY [Starting Date] DESC ) SET @strYear = '(SELECT '+convert(varchar,@firstYear)+'+SUM('+@strFiscal+')-1 FROM ['+@strTableName+'] WHERE ' + @strPeriodStart + '<=x.' + @strPeriodStart + ')' SET @strSQLCommand = 'SELECT YrIdx*100 + PeriodInYear as [Period.PeriodId], Name as [Period.Name], YrIdx as [Period.Year], PeriodInYear as [Period.PeriodInYear], PStart as [Period.PeriodStart], PEnd as [Period.PeriodEnd], PStart as [Period.PeriodStart2], PEnd as [Period.PeriodEnd2], [New Fiscal Year] as [Period.NewFiscalYear], [Closed] as [Period.Closed] FROM ( SELECT *, (select count(*) from ( SELECT ' + @strPeriodStart + ' as PStart, ' + @strYear + ' as YrIdx FROM ['+@strTableName+'] x ) i where i.PStart<=p.[PStart] and i.YrIdx=p.YrIdx) as PeriodInYear FROM ( SELECT ' + @strPeriodStart + ' as PStart, Name,'+@strFiscal+' as [New Fiscal Year],[Closed],' + @strPeriodEnd + ' as PEnd, ' + @strYear + ' as YrIdx FROM ['+@strTableName+'] x ) p ) r' END Exec(@strSQLCommand)
